children.subject: Hi! Thanks for responding—I just updated the answer with some more details about myself/my interests.
What sorts of things could I work on with the knowledge from 194-26 versus the knowledge from 184?

I took 194-26 last semester and am taking 184 this semester. Both are excellently taught and primarily project-based, and with a similar workload too. For 184 if you don't already know C++ you might need to spend a few hours learning it. While there is some overlap, the difference is that 194-26 focuses a lot more on image processing techniques and some computer vision, while 184 is a traditional computer graphics class that focuses on things like transforms, textures, ray tracing, and simulation. It might be helpful to people answering if we knew what you were interested in/what you want to work on.
